      "content": "i hear you on the climate part, but saying those mining issues are just \"manageable challenges\" feels like you're brushing them off a bit. some people argue that the environmental damage from mining and the waste/pollution from turbine blades is much more permanent and harder to fix than just switching fuel sources. isn't it also controversial to call one \"catastrophic\" and the other \"manageable\" when we dont actually know the full long-term impact of huge-scale renewable infrastructure?",
